.TH GH-REFRESH-CONTRIBUTORS 1 "2026-02-13" "gh-refresh-contributors 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
gh-refresh-contributors \- force GitHub to refresh the repository contributors list
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gh-refresh-contributors
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B gh-refresh-contributors
temporarily renames the repository default branch (e.g. \fImain\fR or \fImaster\fR)
to a temporary name and renames it back. This triggers GitHub to refresh the
repository contributors list shown on the web interface.
.PP
Run from the root of a git repository whose \fIorigin\fR remote points to the
GitHub repository. Requires the GitHub CLI (\fBgh\fR(1)) to be installed and
authenticated (\fBgh auth login\fR).
.PP
The temporary branch must exist on the remote before GitHub can set it as
default, so the script pushes the temporary branch first, then sets it as
default. At the end the remote temporary branch is deleted. The script checks
the current state before each step and can resume if interrupted (e.g.
default branch already set to the temporary name).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-b\fR, \fB\-\-branch\fR \fINAME\fR
Branch to use as the default branch. If omitted, auto-detected from the
remote (prefers \fIorigin/main\fR, then \fIorigin/master\fR).
.TP
\fB\-t\fR, \fB\-\-tmp-branch\fR \fINAME\fR
Temporary branch name used during the refresh. Default:
\fItemp-refresh-branch\fR.
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Enable verbose logging to stderr.
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Reduce verbosity. Repeat to reduce further.
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print usage and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success; non-zero on error (invalid options, not a git repo, \fBgh\fR
not authenticated, or failure during branch rename/push).
